SECTION 4 — AUDIENCE INTELLIGENCE
Who they are:

Adults (25–60) who have had nail fungus previously or are actively treating it and want to prevent recurrence. Secondary: health-conscious individuals who visit gyms, pools, or salons regularly and are aware of their risk. Not a beginner audience — they know what nail fungus is. They want specific, actionable steps.
What they want from this post:

A clear, trustworthy list of prevention steps that goes beyond "keep nails dry." Specifically: what to do after treatment is done, how to handle footwear, what to look for in a salon, and whether lifestyle factors (immune health, diet) actually matter.
What frustrates them:

Generic tip-list articles that say nothing beyond washing feet
No guidance on what to do if they've already been through treatment
Conflicting advice on nail polish (can they wear it or not?)
No mention of shoes as a re-infection vector

